question: How many total writing implements (pens, pencils) are visible on surfaces across all rooms? Answer with one option from [0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5+], e.g., 0
What is the total number of pillows across all rooms? Answer with one option from [1-3, 4-6, 7-9, 10-12, 13+], e.g., 1-3
In the living room, what object is located directly on the sofa? Choose one from [pillow, remote control, blanket, book, laptop, nothing], e.g., blanket

Where is the alarm clock located? Answer with the format 'room name, object name'. Choose from: ROOMS: [bedroom with small bed, bedroom with large bed, living room, office, kitchen] OBJECTS: [nightstand, bed, dresser, desk, side table, shelf] Example: ROOMS: bedroom with small bed, OBJECTS: nightstand
Which of the following items is NOT located on the  table in the living room? Choose one from [plate, book, pen, pencil, laptop], e.g., plate
A book is located on a dresser. In which room is this dresser? Choose one from [bedroom with small bed, bedroom with large bed, living room, hallway, office], e.g., bedroom with small bed
Which room has the most writing utensils? Choose one from [living room, kitchen, bedroom with small bed, bedroom with large bed, bathroom], e.g., living room

Which major surface in the entire space is the most cluttered (holds the greatest number of pickupable items)? Choose one from [kitchen counter, dining table, coffee table, office desk, bedroom dresser], e.g., dining table

Comparing the two bedrooms, which object is in the bedroom with the small bed but NOT in the bedroom with the large bed? Choose one from [desk lamp, laptop, alarm clock, mug, television, book], e.g., desk lamp

To both write a note with a pen and use a laptop, which single room has both items available on open surfaces? Choose one from [living room, kitchen, bedroom with the small bed, bedroom with the large bed, office, none], e.g., living room
